OL,6,FSo small were some bone fragments that
OL,7,Fthey could not be used in a
OL,8,Fpainstaking reconstruction of the
OL,9,Fskull which was carried out by
OL,10,Fforensic experts. Some pieces,
OL,11,Fincluding a large section of cranium,
OL,12,Fwere never found.
OL,14,FFurther trauma injuries to Mr Taylor's
OL,15,Felbow suggested he may have tried to
OL,16,Fdefend himself from attack. The
OL,17,Fpathologist concluded his injuries
OL,18,Fcould have been caused by a claw
OL,19,Fhammer.
